    "details" : {
      "en" : {
        "id" : "en",
        "purpose" : "To determine the T, N, and M categories and the final TNM stage group for hepatocellular carcinoma of the liver.",
        "keywords" : [
          "tnm",
          "tumour",
          "node",
          "metastasis",
          "liver",
          "hepatocellular",
          "carcinoma",
          "cancer",
          "hcc",
          "staging"
        ],
        "use" : "Use to classify hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) of the liver according to the TNM system based on a minimal set of categorical clinical inputs.\n\nThe guideline evaluates the following variables:\n\n- Primary tumor assessability\n\n- Presence or absence of a detectable primary tumor\n\n- Tumor pattern (solitary ≤ 2 cm, solitary > 2 cm with/without vascular invasion, multiple tumors none > 5 cm, multiple tumors any > 5 cm)\n\n- Presence of major vascular invasion, invasion of adjacent organs (except gallbladder), or visceral peritoneum perforation\n\n- Regional lymph node assessability\n\n- Regional lymph node metastasis\n\n- Presence of distant metastasis\n\nBased on these inputs, the guideline assigns:\n\n- T category: TX, T0, T1a, T1b, T2, T3, or T4\n\n- N category: NX, N0, or N1\n\n- M category: M0 or M1\n\nFinally, the guideline determines the TNM stage group:\n\n- Stage IA: T1a N0 M0\n\n- Stage IB: T1b N0 M0\n\n- Stage II: T2 N0 M0\n\n- Stage IIIA: T3 N0 M0\n\n- Stage IIIB: T4 N0 M0\n\n- Stage IVA: Any T N1 M0\n\n- Stage IVB: Any T Any N M1",
        "misuse" : "Not to be used for staging cholangiocarcinoma or other liver malignancies that have separate TNM classifications.",
        "copyright" : "© Cambio CDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details" : {
      "references" : "Regionala cancercentrum i samverkan. Nationellt vårdprogram levercellscancer: Kapitel 9 Kategorisering av tumören. Kunskapsbanken, 2024. Available at: https://kunskapsbanken.cancercentrum.se/diagnoser/levercellscancer/vardprogram/kategorisering-av-tumoren/\n\nBrierley JD, Gospodarowicz MK, Wittekind C, editors. TNM classification of malignant tumours. 8th ed. Hoboken (NJ): Wiley Blackwell; 2017",
      "en" : "A structured guideline used to determine the TNM (Tumour-Node-Metastasis) classification and stage grouping for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) of the liver, based on defined clinical input parameters."
    }
  },
